**Provides ASCII banner display, styled terminal output helpers, and post-install guidance messages for the installer using picocolors.**

## Exports

- `VERSION: string` — Package version read from package.json via `getVersion()`
- `displayBanner(): void` — Prints green ASCII art "ARE" logo with version and tagline
- `showHelp(): void` — Displays usage text, CLI flags (`--runtime`, `-g`, `-l`, `-u`, `--force`, `-q`, `-h`), and example commands
- `showSuccess(msg: string): void` — Prints message with green checkmark prefix
- `showError(msg: string): void` — Prints message with red X prefix
- `showWarning(msg: string): void` — Prints message with yellow exclamation prefix
- `showInfo(msg: string): void` — Prints message with cyan arrow prefix
- `showNextSteps(runtime: string, filesCreated: number): void` — Displays post-install workflow steps (7 commands: `/are-help`, `/are-init`, `/are-discover`, `/are-generate`, `/are-update`, `/are-specify`, `/are-clean`) with GitHub docs link

## Dependencies

- `picocolors` — Terminal color formatting via `pc.green()`, `pc.red()`, `pc.yellow()`, `pc.cyan()`, `pc.dim()`, `pc.bold()`
- `../version.js` — `getVersion()` reads package.json version field

## Design Pattern

Stateless helper module exporting pure functions for installer UI. All functions write directly to `console.log()` without return values. Banner uses 7-line ASCII art block with Unicode box-drawing characters. Help text follows standard CLI pattern: Usage → Options → Examples. Message helpers prefix with colored symbols (✓ ✗ ! >) for visual consistency.